I've been going to Cafe Renaissance ever since they opened about 30 years ago and to me it has always been the standard by which all kosher dairy cafes should be measured. I was just there a few weeks ago for lunch and I'm happy to say it has still got it. The food is definitely a notch above other kosher dairy cafes in Brooklyn. However I have to acknowledge that I have found in general the quality of food at dairy restaurants in Brooklyn has gone down significantly in recent years. So I'm giving this cafe 4 out of 5 stars because I feel the place has suffered a bit as a result and the overall elegance and exclusive feel of the place is lacking somewhat. Service was prompt and friendly but the whole feel is more "fast food" than upscale cafe. I think it needs a little improvement. But the food is still terrific!

Cafe renaissance is an okay dairy restausrant with prices that would only be justified for a great restaurant.  It’s a busy place so the food is generally always fresh but with that the service is lacking. Understaffed and overwhelmed is the status quo. The menu lacks enough healthy choices and most of the appetizers we ordered are oily and just average. the one good one was the eggplant appetizer. As a main dish I ordered the Chilean sea bass. Albeit being a very small portion of fish it was actually good. I asked for it pan seared without any sauces put on top and it was delicious. The side dishes it came with it were Average at best and also pathetically small.
